  "description": "This dataset comprises electroencephalography (EEG) recordings from 30 subjects performing a Multiple Object Monitoring (MOM) task. The MOM task is a visual attention paradigm requiring simultaneous tracking of multiple moving objects. EEG data were collected to investigate neural correlates of divided attention and object tracking mechanisms during dynamic visual scenes.",
